awd_abstract_narration: The objective of this study is to further verify the feasibility                of applying breakout geometry to underground excavation in real                 rocks. a large scale polyaxial testing machine will be used in                  order to eliminate all boundary effects on the measured                         excavation response . A Finite Element code, capable of elasto-                 plastic analysis, will be used in order to numerically model the                breakout phenomenon and determine the strength of various                       excavation geometries. The numerical model will also be used for                generation of database which would contain the most stable                      excavation geometries under different stress conditions and for                 various rock types. These data will provide guidelines in real                  practice for modification or design of Tunnel Boring Machines                   (TBM).
